  "agbContent": "Terms and Conditions of SKTG-Marketing\r\n1. General Information and Scope\r\n1.1 SKTG-Marketing operates the website www.sktg-marketing.de (referred to as \"Website\") and may provide associated services (referred to as \"Services\"). These Terms and Conditions (T&C) govern the use of the Website and Services.\r\n\r\n1.2 By accessing or using the Website and Services, you (the \"User\") agree to these T&C. If you do not agree, you must not use the Website or Services.\r\n\r\n1.3 SKTG-Marketing reserves the right to modify these T&C at any time. Users will be notified of changes via the Website or email. Continued use of the Services after such notification constitutes acceptance of the modified T&C.\r\n\r\n2. Eligibility and Use\r\n2.1 Users must be at least 18 years old or have explicit consent from a legal guardian to use the Website or Services.\r\n\r\n2.2 Certain Services may require account registration. User accounts are personal and non-transferable. SKTG-Marketing reserves the right to verify the information provided during registration.\r\n\r\n2.3 Users are responsible for ensuring that their use of the Website and Services complies with applicable laws and regulations.\r\n\r\n3. Offerings by SKTG-Marketing\r\n3.1 SKTG-Marketing provides marketing services and tools available through the Website. Additional information about these Services is provided directly on the Website.\r\n\r\n3.2 SKTG-Marketing continuously improves its offerings. Features or content may be added, replaced, or removed as part of this process without prior notice.\r\n\r\n4. Payment and Fees\r\n4.1 Certain Services may require payment. The applicable fees and terms will be provided at the time of purchase.\r\n\r\n4.2 Payments must be made using the methods specified on the Website. All fees are non-refundable unless otherwise stated in these T&C or required by applicable law.\r\n\r\n4.3 SKTG-Marketing reserves the right to suspend or terminate access to Services if payments are not completed as required.\r\n\r\n5. Right of Withdrawal (Consumers Only)\r\n5.1 If you are a consumer under Section 13 of the German Civil Code (BGB), you have the right to withdraw from a contract within 14 days without giving a reason.\r\n\r\n5.2 The withdrawal period begins on the date the contract is concluded. To exercise this right, you must inform SKTG-Marketing via a clear statement (e.g., email or post). You may use the sample withdrawal form provided below but are not required to do so.\r\n\r\n5.3 Your right of withdrawal expires prematurely if the Service is fully delivered with your express consent and acknowledgment that withdrawal rights are waived upon full performance.\r\n\r\n5.4 Sample Withdrawal Form:\r\n\r\nTo: SKTG-Marketing, www.sktg-marketing.de\/contact\r\nI\/we hereby withdraw from the contract for the purchase of the following goods (*) \/ provision of the following service (*):\r\nOrdered on ______________ \/ Received on ______________\r\nName: ______________\r\nAddress: ______________\r\nDate: ______________\r\n\r\n6. Liability and Disclaimer\r\n6.1 SKTG-Marketing is not liable for damages resulting from the use of the Website or Services unless caused by willful misconduct or gross negligence.\r\n\r\n6.2 SKTG-Marketing\u2019s liability is limited to foreseeable damages typical for this type of agreement. Indirect or consequential damages are excluded to the extent permitted by law.\r\n\r\n6.3 Users are responsible for ensuring that their devices or systems are compatible with the Website and Services.\r\n\r\n7. Privacy and Data Protection\r\n7.1 SKTG-Marketing processes personal data in accordance with its Privacy Policy and applicable data protection laws.\r\n\r\n7.2 By using the Website or Services, Users consent to the collection, storage, and processing of their personal data as outlined in the Privacy Policy.\r\n\r\n8. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution\r\n8.1 These T&C are governed by the laws of Germany, excluding its conflict of law rules.\r\n\r\n8.2 Any disputes arising out of or in connection with these T&C shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in Frankfurt, Germany.\r\n\r\n8.3 SKTG-Marketing complies with the European Commission's Online Dispute Resolution (ODR) platform, accessible via this link. However, SKTG-Marketing does not participate in dispute resolution proceedings before consumer arbitration boards.\r\n\r\n9. Termination of Use\r\n9.1 SKTG-Marketing reserves the right to suspend or terminate access to the Website or Services at any time if a User breaches these T&C or engages in illegal or inappropriate behavior.\r\n\r\n9.2 Users may terminate their use of the Services by ceasing access and deleting any associated accounts.\r\n\r\n10. Contact Information\r\nFor inquiries or concerns, please contact:\r\n\r\nSKTG-Marketing\r\nWebsite: www.sktg-marketing.de\/contact\r\nEmail: info@sktg-marketing.de",
  "dataPrivacy": "Privacy Policy",
  "dataPrivacyContent": "Privacy Policy \u2013 BackQuest\r\nLast updated: 07.04.2025\r\n\r\nWelcome to BackQuest. Your privacy is important to us. This policy explains how we collect, store, and use your personal and health-related data.\r\n\r\nController (Responsible for Data Processing)\r\nTimo Geiling\r\nSKTG-Marketing\r\nNiederw\u00F6llst\u00E4dter Str. 14\r\n61184 Karben\r\nEmail: backquest@outlook.com\r\n\r\n1. Data Collection\r\nWe collect the following data:\r\n\r\nUsername\r\n\r\nEncrypted password\r\n\r\nAge\r\n\r\nHeight\r\n\r\nWeight\r\n\r\nSport preferences\r\n\r\nBack pain indicators\r\n\r\nWe do not collect:\r\n\r\nLocation\r\n\r\nContact information\r\n\r\nPayment or financial data\r\n\r\n2. Health Data Notice\r\nSome of the collected data (such as weight, age, and pain indicators) may be considered health data under the GDPR. We only process such data with your explicit consent (Article 9(2)(a) GDPR), to provide personalized training and wellness recommendations.\r\n\r\n3. Data Storage & Security\r\nYour data is securely stored on Google Cloud infrastructure.\r\n\r\nWe use encrypted transmission and secure authentication for all data.\r\n\r\nPersonal data is retained until you request account deletion.\r\n\r\nGeneral training usage data may be stored permanently for service improvement.\r\n\r\n4. Third-Party Services\r\nWe use Google Cloud to operate our backend systems.\r\n\r\nWe do not use analytics, advertising, or external tracking services.\r\n\r\nWe do not share your data with any third parties.\r\n\r\n5. User Rights\r\nYou have the right to:\r\n\r\nRequest data deletion by contacting: backquest@outlook.com\r\n\r\nEdit your profile \u2013 however, personalized usage history may not be reset due to system integrity.\r\n\r\n6. Cookies & Tracking\r\nBackQuest does not use cookies or any third-party tracking tools.\r\n\r\nWe do not track users across apps, websites, or devices.\r\n\r\n7. Legal Compliance\r\nWe comply with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).\r\n\r\nOur primary user base is located in Germany and the EU.\r\n\r\nFor privacy-related questions, please contact: backquest@outlook.com\r\n\r\n",
